false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 95, "created": 1781305488000, "id": "2065571047995285995", "video": {"preview": "https://pbs.twimg.com/amplify_video_thumb/2065570960149729280/img/NM53nvDtwKPzDEgc.jpg", "mpeg": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2065570960149729280/pl/3hfk-nynzggpwVy_.m3u8?v=f82", "aspectRatio": [9, 16], "heightRatio": 177, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2065570960149729280/vid/avc1/320x568/KCM0SePC5v0P4vgT.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2044584013906513920/nNInjrz9_normal.jpg", "displayName": "DocumentingLibs", "username": "HistorianUSA1"}, "content": "This Norwegian kid visiting the US for the World Cup is straight-up floored by In-N-Out. \ud83d\ude02\n\nFrom struggling through the order (\u201cthree burgers\u2026 only bread and meat!\u201d) to devouring it and calling it \u201cDelicious!\u201d \u2014 pure joy.\n\nEuropeans come here and realize America\u2019s high-quality", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 4313}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsrzdLQW", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 21, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8678068, "raw_content": "Our Enduring Symbol of Freedom\r\n\r\nLess than a year after the Declaration of Independence, with the Revolutionary War raging, the Continental Congress took a bold step to give the new nation a flag of its own. On June 14, 1777, they passed the first Flag Resolution:\r\n\r\n*Resolved, That the flag of the United States be thirteen stripes alternate red and white, that the union be thirteen stars, white in a blue field, representing a new constellation*.\r\n\r\n", "author": "Bullet3250", "created": 1781361405129, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Steve56775", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "June 14 - FLAG DAY - Honoring the Stars and Stripes \u2013 Our Enduring Symbol of Freedom\r\n\r\n This June 14, as we celebrate Flag Day, we pause to honor one of America\u2019s most powerful and unifying symbols: the Stars and Stripes.\r\n", "last_comment_created": 1781361776962, "content": "<p>Our Enduring Symbol of Freedom</p>\n<p>Less than a year after the Declaration of Independence, with the Revolutionary War raging, the Continental Congress took a bold step to give the new nation a flag of its own. On June 14, 1777, they passed the first Flag Resolution:</p>\n<p><em>Resolved, That the flag of the United States be thirteen stripes alternate red and white, that the union be thirteen stars, white in a blue field, representing a new constellation</em>.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 1, "score_up": 21, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2065478746115551632", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsrxOCPY", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 947, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8676620, "raw_content": "", "author": "PiratePatriotParrot", "created": 1781286937912, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "okboomer59", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsrxOCPY.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/i/status